{"title_page": "Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n", "text_new": "{{Expand Spanish|date=February 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n\n| image = Aitana sanchez.jpg\n| birth_name = Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n de Angelis<ref>[http://www.decine21.com/Perfiles/Aitana-Sanchez-Gijon Full name]</ref>\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1968|11|5}}\n| birth_place = Rome, Italy\n| height = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| yearsactive = 1986 \u2013 present\n| homepage =\n| academyawards = \n| occupation = [[Actor|Actress]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|Guillermo Papim Luccadane<br>|2002}}\n| children = 2\n}}\n'''Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n''' (born 5 November 1968 in [[Rome]], Italy) is a Spanish film actress.\n\nShe was born Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n de Angelis in Rome, to father  \u00c1ngel S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n Mart\u00ednez, a history professor, and Italian mother, Fiorella de Angelis, a mathematics professor. She grew up in Spain.\n\nBest known for playing dramatic roles in Spain, S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n first became known internationally for her portrayal of Victoria Aragon, a pregnant and abandoned [[Mexican-American]] winegrower's daughter who is helped by travelling salesman Paul Sutton ([[Keanu Reeves]]) in ''[[A Walk in the Clouds]]'' (1995).\n\nShe has since built a reputation as an international star in films such as [[Manuel Gomez Pereira]]'s ''[[Boca a Boca]]'' (1996), [[Bigas Luna]]'s ''[[The Chambermaid on the Titanic]]'' (1997), [[Jaime Ch\u00e1varri]]'s ''Sus Ojos Se Cerraron'' (1998), [[Gabriele Salvatores]]' adaptation of the [[Niccol\u00f2 Ammaniti]] novel ''[[I'm Not Scared]]'' (2003) and [[Brad Anderson (film director)|Brad Anderson]]'s ''[[The Machinist]]'' (2004).\n\n[[Image:MarioVargasLlosaAitanaSanchezGijon.jpg|thumb|400px|Atiana S\u00e1nchez Gij\u00f3n with [[Mario Vargas Llosa]], actor and writer of \"Los cuentos de la peste\", [[Teatro Espa\u00f1ol (Madrid)|Madrid]], [[Madrid]] (2015).]]\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Romanza final (Gayarre)]]'' (1986)\n* ''[[Bajarse al moro (Elena)]]'' (1989) <ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bajarse_al_moro</ref>\n* ''[[A Walk in the Clouds]]'' (1995)\n* ''[[Boca a Boca]]'' (1996)\n* ''[[The Chambermaid on the Titanic]]'' (1997)\n* ''[[Love Walked In (1997 film)|Love Walked In]]'' (1997)\n* ''Sus Ojos Se Cerraron'' (1998)\n* ''[[Jealousy (1999 film)|Jealousy]]'' (1999)\n* ''[[My Sweet]]'' (2001)\n* ''[[I'm Not Scared]]'' (2003)\n* ''[[The Machinist]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[The Whore and the Whale]]'' (2004)\n* ''[[The Backwoods]]'' (2006)\n* ''The Nautical Chart'' (2007)\n* ''Oviedo Express'' (2007)\n* ''Tell Me About Love'' (2008)\n* ''The Frost'' (2009)\n* ''Maktub'' (2011)\n* ''[[Conquistadores: Adventvm]]'' (2017) as [[Isabel de Castilla]] on [[Cero (TV channel)|Cero]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.movistarplus.es/ficha/conquistadores-adventvm-t1?tipo=E&id=1439022 |title=Conquistadores Adventvm |date=2017 |access-date=January 13, 2018 |work=[[Movistar+]] |language=es}}</ref>\n* ''Thi Mai, Rumbo a VietNam'' (2018)\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=0845209|name=Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sanchez-Gijon, Aitana}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century Spanish actresses]]\n[[Category:Spanish film actresses]]\n[[Category:Italian emigrants to Spain]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Rome]]\n[[Category:Actresses of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:21st-century Spanish actresses]]\n[[Category:Spanish people of Italian descent]]\n\n\n{{spain-film-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Expand Spanish|date=February 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n\n| image = Aitana sanchez.jpg\n| birth_name = Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n de Angelis<ref>[http://www.decine21.com/Perfiles/Aitana-Sanchez-Gijon Full name]</ref>\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1968|11|5}}\n| birth_place = Rome, Italy\n| height = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| yearsactive = 1986 \u2013 present\n| homepage =\n| academyawards = \n| occupation = [[Actor|Actress]]\n| spouse = Guillermo Papim Luccadane <small>(2002 \u2013 present)</small>\n| children = Teo <small>(b. 2001)</small><br/>Bruna <small>(b. 2004)</small>\n| parents = \u00c1ngel S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n Mart\u00ednez (father)<br/>Fiorella de Angelis (mother)\n| relatives = Eloy S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n de Angelis (brother)\n}}\n'''Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n''' (born 5 November 1968 in [[Rome]], Italy) is a Spanish film actress.\n\nShe was born Aitana S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n de Angelis in Rome, to father  \u00c1ngel S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n Mart\u00ednez, a history professor, and Italian mother, Fiorella de Angelis, a mathematics professor. She grew up in Spain.\n\nBest known for playing dramatic roles in Spain, S\u00e1nchez-Gij\u00f3n first became known internationally for her portrayal of Victoria Aragon, a pregnant and abandoned [[Mexican-American]] winegrower's daughter who is helped by travelling salesman Paul Sutton ([[Keanu Reeves]]) in ''[[A Walk in the Clouds]]'' (1995).\n\nShe has since built a reputation as an international star in films such as [[Manuel Gomez Pereira]]'s ''[[Boca a Boca]]'' (1996), [[Bigas Luna]]'s ''[[The Chambermaid on the Titanic]]'' (1997), [[Jaime Ch\u00e1varri]]'s ''Sus Ojos Se Cerraron'' (1998), [[Gabriele Salvatores]]' adaptation of the [[Niccol\u00f2 Ammaniti]] novel ''[[I'm Not Scared]]'' (2003) and [[Brad Anderson (film director)|Brad Anderson]]'s ''[[The Machinist]]'' (2004).\n\n[[Image:MarioVargasLlosaAitanaSanchezGijon.jpg|thumb|400px|Atiana S\u00e1nchez Gij\u00f3n with [[Mario Vargas Llosa]], actor and writer of \"Los cuentos de la peste\", [[Teatro Espa\u00f1ol (Madrid)|Madrid]], [[Madrid]] (2015).]]\n\n==Selected filmography==\n* ''[[Romanza final (Gayarre)]]'' (1986)\n* ''[[Bajarse al moro (Elena)]]'