{"title_page": "Spanish ship Princesa (1750)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=\n|Ship caption=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=\n|Ship country=Spain\n|Ship flag=[[File:Bandera de Espa\u00f1a 1760-1785.svg|50px|Spanish Navy Ensign]]\n|Ship name=''Princesa''\n|Ship ordered=\n|Ship builder=\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=1750\n|Ship acquired=\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship in service=\n|Ship out of service=\n|Ship renamed=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship reinstated=\n|Ship honours=\n|Ship captured=16 January 1780, by Royal Navy\n|Ship fate=\n|Ship status=\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=title\n|Ship country=Great Britain\n|Ship flag=[[File:Naval Ensign of Great Britain (1707-1800).svg|60px|Royal Navy Ensign]]\n|Ship name=HMS ''Princessa''\n|Ship ordered=\n|Ship builder=\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=\n|Ship acquired=16 January 1780\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship in service=\n|Ship out of service=\n|Ship renamed=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship reinstated=\n|Ship honours=\n|Ship captured=\n|Ship fate=Broken up, 1809\n|Ship status=\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n|Hide header=\n|Header caption=<ref name=\"Lavery-SoLvol1\">Lavery, Ships of the Line vol.1. p182.</ref>\n|Ship class=70-gun [[third rate]] [[ship of the line]]\n|Ship tons burthen=1966\n|Ship length=170 ft 2\u00bd in (51.9 m) (gundeck)\n|Ship beam=51 ft 2 in (15.6 m)\n|Ship draught=\n|Ship hold depth=22 ft 1 in (6.7 m)\n|Ship sail plan=[[Full rigged ship]]\n|Ship propulsion=Sails\n|Ship complement=\n|Ship armament=70 guns of various weights of shot\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n|}\n\n'''''Princesa''''' was a 70-gun, two deck, [[ship of the line]] of the [[Spanish Navy]], launched in 1750.\n\nShe fought at the [[Battle of Cape St. Vincent (1780)|Battle of Cape St Vincent]] in 1780, where she was captured by Admiral [[George Rodney]] of the [[Royal Navy]]. She was then recommissioned in England as the [[third rate]] '''HMS ''Princessa'''''.\n\nOn 12 April 1782 she was the flagship of the blue squadron at the [[Battle of the Saintes]] with Admiral [[Francis Samuel Drake]] on board (but under overall control of Admiral [[George Rodney]] of the white squadron.<ref>Famous Fighters of the Fleet, Edward Fraser, 1904, p.106</ref>\n\nFrom 1784 she was employed as a [[sheer hulk]], and she was broken up in 1809.\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n{{refbegin}}\n* Lavery, Brian (2003) ''The Ship of the Line \u2013 Volume 1: The development of the battlefleet 1650\u20131850.'' Conway Maritime Press. {{ISBN|0-85177-252-8}}.\n{{refend}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Princesa (1780)}}\n[[Category:Ships of the line of the Spanish Navy|Princesa (1750)]]\n[[Category:Ships of the line of the Royal Navy]]\n[[Category:1750 ships]]\n\n\n{{UK-line-ship-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2016}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n|Ship image=\n|Ship caption=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=\n|Ship country=Spain\n|Ship flag=[[File:Bandera de Espa\u00f1a 1760-1785.svg|50px|Spanish Navy Ensign]]\n|Ship name=''Princesa''\n|Ship ordered=\n|Ship builder=\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=1750\n|Ship acquired=\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship in service=\n|Ship out of service=\n|Ship renamed=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship reinstated=\n|Ship honours=\n|Ship captured=16 January 1780, by Royal Navy\n|Ship fate=\n|Ship status=\n|Ship notes=\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=title\n|Ship country=Great Britain\n|Ship flag=[[File:Naval Ensign of Great Britain (1707-1800).svg|60px|Royal Navy Ensign]]\n|Ship name=HMS ''Princessa''\n|Ship ordered=\n|Ship builder=\n|Ship laid down=\n|Ship launched=\n|Ship acquired=16 January 1780\n|Ship commissioned=\n|Ship decommissioned=\n|Ship in service=\n|Ship out of service=\n|Ship renamed=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship reinstated=\n|Ship honours=\n|Ship captured=\n|Ship fate=Broken up